{{etyl|enm}} {{term|mowen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|mawan|māwan|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|mēanan}} (cf. Dutch {{term|maaien|lang=nl}}, German {{term|mähen|lang=de}}, Danish {{term|meje}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|h₂meh₁}}- ‘to mow, reap’ (cf. Hittite {{term|hamesha|lang=hit}} ‘spring/early summer’, literally, ‘mowing time’, Ancient Greek (poetic) {{term||amân}})

====Verb====
{{en-verb|mows|mowing|mowed|'''[[mowed]] '''or''' [[mown]]'''}}

# To cut something (especially grass or crops) [[down]] or [[knock]] down.
#: ''He '''mowed''' the [[lawn]]''.

